-- South African Coal Export Prices Fall to Lowest in Three Years
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-10-29T14:04:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-29/south-african-coal-export-prices-fall-to-lowest-in-three-years.html
Coal export prices at  South Africa ’s
 Richards Bay , the continent’s biggest terminal for shipping the
fuel, dropped to the lowest level in almost three years.  Coal for  immediate delivery  declined $1.89, or 2.3 percent,
to $80.46 a metric ton in the week to Oct. 26, according to IHS
McCloskey data on Bloomberg. That’s the lowest since Dec. 25,
2009.  The price is quoted on a free-on-board basis, which
excludes delivery costs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw at 
 mstrzelecki1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson in London at 
 lpaulsson@bloomberg.net  